  "text": "by TGF-\u03b21. EMT is known to play an important role in cancer metastasis [CITATION_1] . Essentially, TGF-\u03b21 has been well reported to induce the process of EMT [CITATION_2] . Fig. 4A shows western blot analysis of TGF-\u03b21 downregulated significantly compared to the control in HCC-LM3 cells after fisetin treatment, dose-dependently (Fig. 4C) . In addition, vimentin ( Fig. 4A  and D ), E-cadherin ( Fig. 4A and E) and N-cadherin (Fig. 4A and F) were apparently reduced due to fisetin administration, which was in line with TGF-\u03b21 expression. Importantly, bromocriptine indicated similar role in suppressing TGF-\u03b21 ( Fig. 4B and G) , vimentin ( Fig. 4B and H ), E-cadherin ( Fig. 4B and I ) and N-cadherin ( Fig. 4B and J) in HCC-LM3 cells. Furthermore, immunofluorescence analysis proved that TGF-\u03b21 could be reduced in fisetin and bromocriptine treat- Fig. 4K and L) . The data above suggested that fisetin could ameliorate liver cancer progression via EMT inhibition through TGF-\u03b21 signaling pathway.",
